  "optimization_hints": [
    "Q1: Full lineitem scan (59M rows, ~985K output rows). Zone-map or bitmap index on l_shipdate for skip. Vectorized aggregation for 6 distinct groups. No sort needed if group keys presorted.",
    "Q3: Three-way join (customer 1.5M → orders 15M → lineitem 60M), cascading filters reduce intermediate results. Semi-join on orders subquery with HAVING to push qualification. Hash join with morsel-parallelism over 64 cores (60M/64 ~= 1M rows/thread).",
    "Q6: Selective lineitem scan (34% × 46% combined ~16% output). Branch-free filtering for discount+quantity predicates. Aggregation to 1 row avoids materialization; only accumulate SUM. Early termination if index available.",
    "Q9: Five-way join through bridge table (partsupp). p_name LIKE %green% filter highly selective (5.3%). Semi-join or bloom filter on part before partsupp join. Late materialization for strings; compute amounts with integers only. Group by nation (25 values) and year (~7 distinct years) = 175 groups.",
    "Q18: Subquery with GROUP BY HAVING on lineitem (59M → ~10K large orders). Convert to semi-join via hash set. Main query three-way join (customer 1.5M → orders → lineitem). Top-100 via partial sort or heap, no full sort.",
    "Global: Parallelize all table scans and joins with 32 threads (64/2 for HT). Lineitem: 60M rows → morsel size ~2M/thread. Compressed disk I/O dominates; use mmap+sequential prefetch. Avoid materialization of large intermediates (orders × lineitem join); fuse with aggregation."
  ],
  "summary": "TPC-H SF10 OLAP workload dominated by lineitem fact table (60M rows) joined with smaller dimensions (orders 15M, customer 1.5M). Q1 is a single-table aggregation (easy), Q3 and Q18 feature cascading joins with selective filters (~48-53% on date ranges), Q6 is a highly selective multi-predicate scan (16%), Q9 involves complex bridge-table joins with string filtering (5%). Execution time bottleneck: Q3/Q18 join fanout (60M lineitem rows processed) and Q9 multi-way join. Key optimizations: (1) morsel-driven parallel scans with 32+ threads, (2) semi-joins and bloom filters to reduce intermediate results, (3) push filters down before joins, (4) late materialization for strings, (5) zone-map skipping on date columns, (6) hash aggregation for low-cardinality groups. Hardware: 64-core Xeon with AVX-512 and 376GB RAM enables vector processing and high-concurrency execution."
